BURGERSFORT- Sekhukhune Modelling and Pageantry Academy recently held the Face of Winter Sekhukhune
competition at the AGS in Steelpoort. The charity-driven event included pageants for seniors, preteens and teenagers. Speaking to Steelburger/Lydenburg News event organiser, Tumi Masilela, said the contestants donated clothing to the needy. “Each contestant had to donate winter clothing as part of entry requirements. The clothes will be handed to the needy people at Mabocha, Maretlagadi Welfare Centre and Rehlahleng Special School.” The winner for the preteen pageants was Zindle Vilakazi, while the winner in the teenage category was Ofentse Talane. The overall winner for the senior pageants was Anastacia Makofane. The organisers said they were pleased with how the event had gone. “The set-up, decor, participants and judges were excellent. We wish to thank sponsors such as Kingdom Management, TTM Foundation, Spur Burgersfort, Rufaro Luxury Lodge and Tingeling Preparatory School for making the event a success.” Masilela urged locals to assist with clothing to be donated to orphanages and disability centers. Those interested
in donating clothing items can contact Masilela on 082 335 8173/072 407 2878.